// A comptime string index past the end surfaces a clean C4002 diagnostic
// instead of silently baking U+0000 into the program. The VM-backed comptime
// evaluator runs `oob()` in the interpreter, whose `.StringIndexAt` host
// arm (vader/vm/host.vader) now traps on an out-of-range index — the trap is
// routed to C4002 by the comptime_vm pass. Regression guard for audit item B4,
// the most serious face of the native↔VM string-OOB divergence : before the
// fix the NUL codepoint was baked in with no diagnostic at all.

module "snippet"

oob :: fn() -> char = "abc"[10]

@comptime
export BAD :: oob()

main :: fn() -> i32 {
    return i32(BAD)
}
